---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import facts from '../../content/facts';
---

<Layout
  title="Verso Data — Coverage"
  description="Distinct prompts per vertical and language. What supports full preference rates, what supports deltas only, and where we're still building depth."
  ogTitle="Verso Data — Coverage"
  ogDescription="What we cover, and where we're still building depth."
  includeScrollReveal
>

<Nav variant="data" />

<main class="vs-wrap vs-page">

  <span class="vs-mono">Coverage</span>
  <h1 class="vs-rise">What we cover, <u>and what we don't.</u></h1>
  <p class="vs-page-lede vs-rise">
    Every cell in the table below represents a vertical–language pair. Cells with sufficient
    depth support full preference rates with confidence intervals. Thinner cells support
    model-vs-model deltas — enough to detect a winner, not enough to publish a stable rate.
    We say which is which.
  </p>

  {facts.coverage && facts.coverage.length > 0 && (
    <section class="vs-block vs-rise">
      <h2>Coverage table</h2>
      <p>Distinct prompts per cell. Updated as the dataset grows.</p>

      <table class="vs-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Vertical</th>
            <th>Language</th>
            <th>Distinct prompts</th>
            <th>Supports</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {facts.coverage.map(cell => (
            <tr>
              <td>{cell.vertical}</td>
              <td>{cell.language}</td>
              <td>{cell.distinctPrompts.toLocaleString()}</td>
              <td class={cell.supports === 'rates' ? 'vs-yes' : 'vs-muted'}>{cell.supports === 'rates' ? 'Full rates' : 'Deltas only'}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>

      {facts.totalDistinctPrompts && (
        <p class="vs-note" style="margin-top:16px">
          Total: <b>{facts.totalDistinctPrompts.toLocaleString()}</b> distinct prompts across
          <b>{facts.modelsCompared}</b> model comparisons{facts.collectionStartDate && <>, since {facts.collectionStartDate}</>}.
        </p>
      )}
    </section>
  )}

  <section class="vs-block vs-rise">
    <h2>What "distinct prompts" means</h2>
    <p>A distinct prompt is a unique user question, deduplicated by semantic similarity. If five users ask "best noise-cancelling headphones" in slightly different words, that counts as one distinct prompt with five paired observations. The metric that matters for statistical power is distinct prompts, not total comparisons — because paired observations on the same prompt are not independent.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="vs-block vs-rise">
    <h2>Rates vs. deltas</h2>
    <div class="vs-two">
      <div>
        <h3>Full rates</h3>
        <p>Cells with enough distinct prompts support a preference rate — "Model A is preferred X% of the time on shopping questions in English" — with a confidence interval narrow enough to be useful. This is the primary deliverable for AI labs running model evaluations.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>Deltas only</h3>
        <p>Thinner cells can still detect which model wins on a given vertical, but the rate estimate is too wide to publish. These cells are useful for directional signal — "Model A outperforms Model B on French travel queries" — but not for reporting a stable number.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="vs-block vs-rise">
    <h2>Growing a thin cell</h2>
    <p>If a cell you care about is thin — or missing entirely — we can recruit for it. Sponsored panels target consenting users in a specific vertical and language. The panel runs for a defined period, the data accumulates, and the cell moves from deltas-only to full rates. This is how we build depth in verticals that don't occur organically at high volume.</p>
    <p style="margin-top:26px">
      <a class="vs-btn" href="mailto:contact@tryverso.ai?subject=Verso%20Data%20—%20sponsored%20panel%20inquiry">
        Inquire about a sponsored panel
        <svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 13 13" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M1 6.5h11M7.5 2l4.5 4.5L7.5 11" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6"/>
        </svg>
      </a>
    </p>
  </section>

</main>

<Footer links={[
  { href: '/data', label: 'Data' },
  { href: '/data/methodology', label: 'Methodology' },
  { href: '/', label: 'Extension' },
  { href: '/privacy', label: 'Privacy' },
  { href: 'mailto:contact@tryverso.ai', label: 'Contact' },
]} />

</Layout>
